    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "It is as if the very air has become too thick to breathe. Every memory of him is a blade, and every prospect of tomorrow is a mountain I simply cannot climb. Is it not strange? To feel so much weight, yet feel so incredibly empty at the same time. I look at the window, at the vast, cold expanse of the night, and I find myself envying its stillness. It seems so much kinder than the noise of a heart that refuses to stop breaking.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
